## Matplotlib

for importing any library we need use pip pakage to install the packages 

pip3 install matplotlib

for import matplotlib.pyplot as plt  importing a package to the python script we need to use 

```python

year = [1950,1970,1990,2010]

pop = [2.519,3.692,5.263,6.972]

plt.plot(year,pop)  #this will create a line chart 

plt.show()               #this will display the charts or plots created

### Scatter Plot

plt..scatter(year,pop)     # this will create an scatter plot

plt.show()
```

    

```python
# Change the line plot below to a scatter plot
plt.scatter(gdp_cap, life_exp)

# Put the x-axis on a logarithmic scale
plt.xscale('log')

# Show plot
plt.show()
```

### Histogram

plt.hist(values,bins=3)

```python
# Create histogram of life_exp data
plt.hist(life_exp,10)

# Display histogram
plt.show()
```

